description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic dietitian to join our adult team and share our busy workload.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The new Medical and Surgical Assessment Centre will be a two-storey extension adjacent to the emergency department (ED) at the front of the hospital and next to Charnley Ward. This will improve the facilities available for our patients ahead of the completion of the new hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work will be varied and include cover to all our wards including work within diabetes and cancer services. You will also be involved with developing nutrition support services (e.g. enteral feeding) and will be part of the Nutrition Multidisciplinary Team. You will have opportunities to have input to the Nutrition Steering Group and help to take forward new initiatives in the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a department of 10 dietitians and one secretary in total, with 6 dietitians covering the adult service. Due to our small numbers and varying working times and days, we have to work well as a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role you will need a degree in Nutrition and Dietetics or equivalent post-graduate qualification and you will need to be registered as a Dietitian with the Health and Care Professions Council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need evidence of post registration training in the form of short courses and study days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
